s congruent with current systematics. Cytochrome\n              b\n              proved useful for species-level delimitation in non-conflicting genera (\n              Eumops\n              ,\n              Dasypterus\n              ,\n              Molossops\n              ) and has infrageneric resolution in more complex lineages (\n              Eptesicus\n              ,\n              Myotis\n              ,\n              Molossus\n              ). We discuss four sources of incongruence that may act separately or in combination: 1) molecular processes, 2) biology, 3) limitations in identification, and 4) errors in the current taxonomy. The present study confirms the general applicability of cytochrome\n              b\n              -based phylogenies in eco-epidemiological studies, but its resolution and reliability depend mainly, but not solely, on the level of genetic differentiation within each bat genus.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Caraballo, Diego A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Montani, Mar\u00eda E.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mart\u00ednez, Leila M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Antoniazzi, Leandro R.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sambrana, Tom\u00e1s C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Fern\u00e1ndez, Camilo", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Cisterna, Daniel M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Beltr\u00e1n, Fernando J.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Colombo, Valeria C.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Yue, Bi-Song", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/d4dc2882c73a3b44e41cdf0950baa41b", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/02d520e5d1d4906a323631e9ec34293ab15adfd78571577934c24a5b39cf482b", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/87BN9X9B", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme"